Interpolation Methods
This project explores numerical interpolation techniques including polynomial interpolation, Newton's divided differences, Hermite interpolation,
and cubic splines. Each problem investigates the accuracy, error, and graphical behavior of different approximation methods through Maple implementations and visual analysis.

The Maple source code for each problem is included in this folder. The accompanying Project 2 PDF contains both the code and its output,
allowing the results to be viewed without downloading or executing the individual files.
